(1, 'Stand Out, Shout Out', 9, 25, 1, 'Stand Out, Shout Out', 'Five Steps to Finding Your Business Identity & Communicating It Effectively', 'http://hosted.mediasite.com/mediasite/Viewer/?peid=630abeaef449435d809b29c94c897ea91d', '', 5, '<p>Marketing can be overwhelming for the small business  owner.Â  Thereâ€™s simply not enough time  and there are way too many marketing options.Â   How do you spend your time on the right marketing strategy and get the  maximum benefit?Â  You must know your  businessâ€™ identity first.Â  Once this is  known, all your other marketing decisions fall into place.Â  This chapter will feature Michelle Lanter  Smith as she discusses the steps to developing your business identity.Â  Sheâ€™ll also disclose her five secrets to  successful marketing: </p>\r\n<p>Secret 1:  Differentiate Your Business<br />\r\nSecret 2:  Target the Ideal Client<br />\r\nSecret 3:  Ask, Ask, then Ask Again<br />\r\nSecret 4:  Strategy before Tactics<br />\r\nSecret 5: Be  Found</p>\r\n<p>After listening to the webinar, youâ€™ll be ready to get  started.Â  Take a look at the SWOT primer  and read the articles to learn why you want to take the time to understand your  businessâ€™ strengths and weaknesses from your customersâ€™ and stakeholdersâ€™  perspectives.</p>\r\n<p>Next steps to complete this chapter:<br />\r\n  Complete your <em>Voice of  the Customer</em> surveys.<br />\r\n  Complete your SWOT planning session with your team.</p>\r\n', '2012-01-31', '2012-03-29 19:31:55', '', 'Michelle Lanter Smith discusses the steps to developing your business identity.Â '),
(2, 'Should I Stay or Should I Grow Now?', 9, 0, 2, 'Should I Stay or Should I Grow Now?', 'Refining Your Elevator Pitch & Taking Your Business to the Next Level webinar*', 'https://amfam.webex.com/ec0605lc/eventcenter/recording/recordAction.do?theAction=poprecord&actname=%2Feventcenter%2Fframe%2Fg.do&apiname=lsr.php&renewticket=0&renewticket=0&actappname=ec0605lc&entappname=url0107lc&needFilter=false&&isurlact=true&entactname=%2FnbrRecordingURL.do&rID=39551827&rKey=391bb166659c8b05&recordID=39551827&rnd=3815507750&siteurl=amfam&SP=EC&AT=pb&format=short', '', 4, '<p>How do you know when it is time to take your business to the next level?Â  Is your business in a position to even consider growth?</p>\r\n<p>In this chapter, our experts will explore business growthâ€”setting your goals and strategically planning for it.Â  Rich Lyons presents a webinar on the importance of assessing your risk and knowing where you stand prior to growth.Â  He discusses how you need to predict your costs and your benefits associated with growth and that you must develop a strong strategy to minimize your risk and maximize your results.Â  </p>\r\n<p>Be sure to take a look at the number of articles from our experts on powering up your business and leading your team to future growth.</p>\r\n<p>Next steps to complete this chapter:</p>\r\n<p>Do a risk-benefit analysis of growing your business now.</p>\r\n', '2012-01-31', '2012-03-31 19:18:56', '', ''),
(3, 'Build a Team for Business Growth ', 9, 0, 2, 'Build a Team for Business Growth ', 'June 30, 2011 Core Webinar 3', 'https://amfam.webex.com/ec0605lc/eventcenter/recording/recordAction.do?theAction=poprecord&actname=%2Feventcenter%2Fframe%2Fg.do&apiname=lsr.php&renewticket=0&renewticket=0&actappname=ec0605lc&entappname=url0107lc&needFilter=false&&isurlact=true&entactname=%2FnbrRecordingURL.do&rID=43195317&rKey=ef217fa3db532f41&recordID=43195317&rnd=9790533068&siteurl=amfam&SP=EC&AT=pb&format=short', '', 4, '<p><strong>Note:</strong> Start at 46:34</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>You launched your small business with excitement, energy, and a staff of one, or maybe two. Youâ€™ve made it past your one year anniversary and know you have something to offer. Youâ€™re ready to turn some of your attention to growing your business but need some additional resources. How do you know when to build your team? </p>\r\n<p>In this chapter, weâ€™ll explore the common questions that small business owners struggle with when figuring out how to grow their company.Â  Should you add a full-time person, part-timers, or interns? How can you create a virtual board to support you in your growth and success? </p>\r\n<p>Small business owners have a lot of options for building their team. Whether you are ready to build now or planning for it down the road, in this chapter youâ€™ll explore the many paths available and what might fit for you.</p>\r\n<p>Next steps to complete this chapter:</p>\r\n<p>Create a list of the additional support you need to support your business growth.</p>\r\n', '2012-01-31', '2012-03-29 20:15:32', '', ''),
(4, 'The Pain-Free Business Plan for Those Who Seek Long-Term Success ', 9, 27, 2, 'Starting Out Right', 'Writing Your Business Plan (2012 webinar)', '/events/view/9', '', 2, '<p>Having a business plan is paramount to your long-term growth. A good business plan conveys the excitement and promise of your business to any potential backer or future stakeholder. In this webinar, with Michael Valentine, The Plan Doctor, learn how to craft a professional. Master the ability to create, amend, or rework your small business planâ€”without the headache.</p>\r\n<p>In this chapter, learn:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>A fresh new blueprint to approach the continuous growth of your businesses</li>\r\n  <li>Why having a well-tailored business plan will lead you to where you want to go</li>\r\n  <li>How to construct a business plan youâ€™ll actually use</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '2012-01-31', '2012-03-26 14:56:19', '', ''),
(5, 'Lead Your Company, Lead Your World', 9, 0, 3, 'Lead Your Company, Lead Your World', 'October 2009 slideshare', 'http://www.slideshare.net/slideshow/embed_code/2180310?rel=0', '', 3, '<p>Leadership is the art of getting work done through others. However, it can sometimes be difficult to lead your team to your desired outcome.Â  Things get in the wayâ€”personal agendas, company cultures, the inability to make difficult decisions.</p>\r\n<p>In this chapter, Dr. Bob Wright explores how leadership evolves as your company grows.Â  In his presentation, he discusses how leaders deal with different personalities, get the most from the lease, build a culture, and become a trusted advisor.Â  He also talks about some of the most common errors that small business leaders face.<br />\r\n  Â To assist entrepreneurs in leading their organization, Dr. Bob discusses a methodology called the ideal state planning processâ€”a powerful tool of visioning and alignment that helps build a fulfilling team culture and assists in conflict management and resolution.</p>\r\n<p>Be sure to also look over the articles from our featured experts Rieva Lesonsky and Stever Robbins. Rieva discusses the need for leadership in the start-up scenario and Stever writes about the need for leaders to fire things up during tough times.</p>\r\n<p>Next steps to complete this chapter:</p>\r\n<p>Take some time to assess your leadership challenges.</p>\r\n', '2012-01-31', '2012-03-29 20:16:46', '', ''),
(10, 'The Truth Be Told', 9, 0, 1, '', 'Discovering Critical Information That Will Distinguish Your Business From Others', 'https://amfam.webex.com/ec0605lc/eventcenter/recording/recordAction.do?theAction=poprecord&actname=%2Feventcenter%2Fframe%2Fg.do&apiname=lsr.php&renewticket=0&renewticket=0&actappname=ec0605lc&entappname=url0107lc&needFilter=false&&isurlact=true&entactname=%2FnbrRecordingURL.do&rID=42939477&rKey=993ebce29dc462c4&recordID=42939477&rnd=3371510371&siteurl=amfam&SP=EC&AT=pb&format=short\r\n', '', 4, '<p><strong>Note:</strong>Core Webinar 1, June 2, 2011 Taking a Closer Look; start at 4:20</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p>In order to understand the real benefit of what you offer  your customers, you need to ask them. In this chapter, Michelle Lanter Smith  will walk you through how you take your customersâ€™ responses from your <em>Voice of the Customer</em> surveys and create  your business identity.Â  Your business  identity is like a bumper sticker for your company.Â  A concise and clear statement, it  communicates your one key benefit that positions your business and  differentiates you from your competition. It all starts with asking your  customers about your strengths and weaknesses and how they benefit from your  product or service.Â  Upon completion of  your business identity, you can easily springboard to the core messages that  you want to include in your marketing communications planning.</p>\r\n<p>To get the most from this chapter, be sure to download the  business identity worksheet prior to listening to the webinar.Â  Then, read the articles to learn why you need  to focus your business message and why you must focus on the benefits you  deliver to your customers and not lose sight of them amongst your daily trials  and tribulations.</p>\r\n<p>Next steps to complete this chapter:</p>\r\n<p>Determine your businessâ€™ sweet spot--complete your business  identity worksheet.</p>\r\n', '2012-03-01', '2012-03-29 19:42:39', '', ''),
(11, 'Sticky Marketing', 9, 0, 1, '', 'Crafting Your Message and Learning How to Make It Stick', 'https://amfam.webex.com/ec0605lc/eventcenter/recording/recordAction.do?theAction=poprecord&actname=%2Feventcenter%2Fframe%2Fg.do&apiname=lsr.php&renewticket=0&renewticket=0&actappname=ec0605lc&entappname=url0107lc&needFilter=false&&isurlact=true&entactname=%2FnbrRecordingURL.do&rID=43195317&rKey=ef217fa3db532f41&recordID=43195317&rnd=2150405203&siteurl=amfam&SP=EC&AT=pb&format=short\r\n', '', 4, '<p><strong>Note:</strong> 2011, Core Webinar 3-- Sticky Business; start at 2:45</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Before you can get your marketing messages out, you need to  build a plan.Â  This chapter features a  webinar with Michelle Lanter Smith in which she reviews a simple, yet effective  marketing plan template that you can use to build your small businessâ€™ marketing  plan.Â  She discusses how you can select  the right tactics to meet your objectives and how you can get your yearâ€™s plan  all down on an easy-to-use excel template. </p>\r\n<p>Also in this chapterâ€™s webinar, Barbara Lopez will teach you  how to craft a message that youâ€™ll use to introduce your business.Â  This is something that youâ€™ll communicate day  in and day out to position your business properly and attract potential  customers.Â  Barbara will take you through  her F.A.R.M. systemâ€”four easy steps to building your elevator pitch.</p>\r\n<p>Finally, your marketing plan should not just be about  finding new customers.Â  Read this  chapterâ€™s articles to help you renew your focus on your current customer base. </p>\r\n<p>Next steps to complete this chapter:</p>\r\n<p>Complete your marketing plan; download the marketing plan  worksheet.</p>\r\n', '2012-03-01', '2012-03-29 19:43:49', '', ''),
(12, 'Marketing on a Limited Budget', 9, 0, 4, '', 'E-marketing & Word of Mouth Techniques that Generate Sales ', 'https://amfam.webex.com/ec0605lc/eventcenter/recording/recordAction.do?theAction=poprecord&actname=%2Feventcenter%2Fframe%2Fg.do&apiname=lsr.php&renewticket=0&renewticket=0&actappname=ec0605lc&entappname=url0107lc&needFilter=false&&isurlact=true&entactname=%2FnbrRecordingURL.do&rID=43331272&rKey=36b8513f3a4a5a73&recordID=43331272&rnd=3007574920&siteurl=amfam&SP=EC&AT=pb&format=short\r\n', '', 4, '<p><strong>Note:</strong> Core Webinar 4, July 14, 2011; start at 2:16</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Some people think that the word marketing equates to &ldquo;money&rdquo;  . . . that is, spending lots of it.Â  But  that&rsquo;s not necessarily the case.Â  In this  chapter, we&rsquo;ll discuss in the webinar and the articles some of the most popular  e-marketing tools such as newsletters, blogging, and social media.Â  In addition, we&rsquo;ll also dive deep into some  really great word-of-mouth techniques that give people something to talk  about.Â Â  Bottom line: if your business  can devise customer experiences that are memorable and out of the ordinary, you  are more likely to get customers to talk about you.</p>\r\n<p>Michelle Lanter Smith will moderate a discussion with social  media gurus Dean DeLisle and Jeannie Walters on how to use some of these  effective small business marketing tools.Â   Also, John Jantsch will give you some excellent tips on leveraging  social media to market your small business.</p>\r\n<p>Next steps to complete this chapter:</p>\r\n<p>Set aside 20 minutes a day to do your social media outreach.</p>\r\n', '2012-03-01', '2012-03-29 19:44:36', '', ''),
(13, 'Leveraging the Power of Twitter and Blogging to Generate Leads', 9, 0, 4, '', 'Leveraging the Power of Twitter and Blogging to Generate Leads', 'http://www.kaltura.com/p/737192/sp/73719200/embedIframeJs/uiconf_id/7642702/partner_id/737192', 'http://www.kaltura.com/index.php/kwidget/cache_st/1332866714/wid/_737192/uiconf_id/7642702/entry_id/1_ptywy0dh', 1, '<p>You can accelerate your business by leveraging the power of  Twitter, Blogs, and E-newsletters.Â  In  this chapter, Dean DeLisleâ€™s webinar demonstrates how you can integrate the  content featured on all three of these social media components.Â  Youâ€™ll also learn how you can leverage each  of their strengths to promote your business content and generate considerable  inbound leads.</p>\r\n<p>While blogging has been around for a while, in this webinar  weâ€™ll show you new techniques for lead generation using your blog and your  social networks. Learn how you can:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>Start a blog and use it wisely to generate leads</li>\r\n  <li>Leverage Twitter to give your blog a super-boost  and generate more clicks</li>\r\n  <li>Get more eyes on your e-mail newsletters</li>\r\n  <li>Promote your business, website, or event on  Twitter</li>\r\n  <li>Connect with others and gain followers on  Twitter</li>\r\n  <li>Covert Twitter and Blog followers to sales</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Next steps to complete this chapter:</p>\r\n<p>Consider starting a WordPress blog or integrating a blog  into your current website.Â  Use your blog  to host your e-newsletter articles.Â   Promote your blog posts with Twitter tweets.</p>\r\n', '2011-04-14', '2012-03-27 16:41:12', '', ''),
