(20, 'Hands-On Virtual Lab. Generating Leads Online with Facebook, LinkedIn and Google', 9, 0, 4, '', 'Generating Leads Online with Facebook, LinkedIn and Google  (2010 Fall Symposium) ', 'http://hosted.mediasite.com/mediasite/Viewer/?peid=ee018d4b9a7f4c849da9f050ebb127591d', '', 5, '<p>Are your sales leads too few and  far between?Â  This chapter is a hands-on  virtual lab to teach you how to use Facebook, LinkedIn, and Google as a lead  generation tool.Â  So open up another  window in your browser and get yourself logged on to your LinkedIn and Facebook  accounts while you listen to this webinar</p>\r\n<p>In this chapter,  Dean DeLisle takes you through the actual steps of much of what he discusses in  Chapter 3.Â Â  Heâ€™ll also tell you his  secrets on how to log in only 20 minutes a day to get maximum results and  convert business from your LinkedIn and Facebook connections.</p>\r\n<p>Next steps to complete this chapter:</p>\r\n<p>Two old/Two new: Each day reach out to two old connections and catch up. Each day make two new connections and start a conversation.  Download SNAP to help you with what to say.</p>\r\n\r\n', '2012-03-05', '2012-03-29 19:46:37', '', ''),
(21, 'LinkedIn Level II ', 9, 0, 4, '', '(Dec. 14 2010 webinar) ', 'https://amfam.webex.com/ec0605lc/eventcenter/recording/recordAction.do?theAction=poprecord&actname=%2Feventcenter%2Fframe%2Fg.do&apiname=lsr.php&renewticket=0&renewticket=0&actappname=ec0605lc&entappname=url0107lc&needFilter=false&&isurlact=true&entactname=%2FnbrRecordingURL.do&rID=41226497&rKey=47cabef1a6167866&recordID=41226497&rnd=1281565028&siteurl=amfam&SP=EC&AT=pb&format=short\r\n', '', 4, '\r\n<p>Are you comfortable with LinkedIn but you want to learn how  to use it even more effectively to generate appointments?Â Â  In this chapter, Dean DeLisle will take your  LinkedIn learning to the next level.Â  Heâ€™ll  teach you how to tune up your LinkedIn profile for maximum impactâ€”both with  your connections and with SEO.Â  Heâ€™ll  show you how you can use LinkedInâ€™s search capabilities to find prospects in  your target audience and add connections to magnify your network to millions  quickly.Â  Finally, Dean will discuss the  importance of recommendations and how you must both give and get them to truly  leverage the power of LinkedIn.</p>\r\n<p>Be sure to download the handouts in this chapter to help you  set up your profiles and give you ideas on how to ask for an appointment with  LinkedIn connections.</p>\r\n<p>Next steps to complete this chapter:</p>\r\n<p>Ask 5 five of your connections in LinkedIn to give you a  recommendation.Â  Be sure to take the time  to write a recommendation back.</p>\r\n', '2012-03-05', '2012-03-26 13:44:04', '', ''),
(22, 'Featured Expert - Social Media for Small Business with John Jantsch', 9, 40, 4, '', 'Featured Expert - Social Media for Small Business with John Jantsch', 'http://www.kaltura.com/index.php/kwidget/cache_st/1333032875/wid/_737192/uiconf_id/7642702/entry_id/1_l1muo00z', 'http://www.kaltura.com/index.php/kwidget/cache_st/1333032875/wid/_737192/uiconf_id/7642702/entry_id/1_l1muo00z', 6, '<p>When used properly, social media can be a great tool to help  your business reach untapped, potential customers and stay connected to current  ones.Â  But there are a few things youâ€™ll  need to know to help you get the most out of social media marketing as well as  your online presence in its entirety.</p>\r\n<p>In this chapter, John Jantsch--small business expert and  author of <em>Duct Tape Marketing</em> and <em>The Referral Engine</em>â€”will break social  media down into easy-to-understand pieces so you can make sense of and make use  of this powerful resource in a way that grows your business.</p>\r\n<p>Listen to Johnâ€™s podcast with Business Accelerator Host,  Euan Ford, for some quick tips on leveraging social media in your  business.Â  Be sure to read Johnâ€™s  articles and e-book <em>Letâ€™s Talk: Social  Media for Small Business</em> for further understanding. </p>\r\n<p>Next steps to complete this chapter:</p>\r\n<p>Take an hour one evening to read John Jantschâ€™s ebook, <em>Letâ€™s Talk: Social Media for Small Business.Â  </em>Decide which activities you can deploy  and make your to-do list.</p>\r\n', '2012-03-05', '2012-03-31 19:21:14', '', ''),
(23, 'How to Acquire Customers on a Small Budget', 9, 0, 6, '', ' (June 22, 2010 webinar; start at 22:49) ', 'https://amfam.webex.com/ec0605lc/eventcenter/recording/recordAction.do?theAction=poprecord&actname=%2Feventcenter%2Fframe%2Fg.do&apiname=lsr.php&renewticket=0&renewticket=0&actappname=ec0605lc&entappname=url0107lc&needFilter=false&&isurlact=true&entactname=%2FnbrRecordingURL.do&rID=39685142&rKey=646f636b676656f4&recordID=39685142&rnd=6778662272&siteurl=amfam&SP=EC&AT=pb&format=short\r\n', '', 4, '<p>For most small business owners, financial resources are very limited. So when you do decide to execute a lead generation project you want to make sure you get the most for your money.Â  In this chapter, we discuss various non-digital lead generation techniques, such as direct mail and PR.</p>\r\n<p>In the webinar and associated articles, Michelle Lanter Smith discusses how you must write a creative brief before you give a project to a designer.Â  Be sure to download her creative brief template so you can build one fast and easy.Â  With special guest, Chris Geimer, she also discloses some direct mail formulas that have proven to work well in yielding results.</p>\r\n<p>Finally, PR is a marketing tactic that many small businesses overlook.Â  In this chapter, weâ€™ll discuss the advantages of PR; the webinar will feature Cesar Rolon, a PR expert who often uses the media to generate leads and awareness for his small business contacts.</p>\r\n<p>Next steps to complete this chapter:</p>\r\n<p>Take a look at a free online PR distribution service such as pr.com.Â  Write up a customer case study or a new product announcement and release it online and to your local or trade publication media.</p>\r\n', '2012-03-05', '2012-03-29 19:47:44', '', ''),
(24, 'Integrating Affordable Tools into Your Marketing ', 9, 0, 6, '', '(August 28, 2009 slideshare) ', 'http://www.slideshare.net/slideshow/embed_code/1921212?rel=0', '', 3, '<p>It seems like everyone has an e-newsletter nowadays. Does that mean you should skip it? Probably not. E-marketing and e-newsletters still provide a very affordable way to reach out to your current customers and prospects.Â  In this chapter, weâ€™ll talk about e-marketing and how you can execute it without it stealing all your time and money.Â  Weâ€™ll also discuss the critical pieces of your e-marketing efforts like your subject line and building your in-house list. Additionally, the webinar in this chapter will discuss search engine optimization and why you should pay particular attention to the words you use in your online content.</p>\r\n<p>Next steps to complete this chapter:</p>\r\n<p>Put a program in place to increase the size of your in-house email list.</p>\r\n', '2012-03-05', '2012-03-29 19:52:11', '', ''),
(25, 'Using Direct Mail, PR, and Advertising to Generate Leads', 9, 25, 6, '', ' (2012 webinar) ', '/events/view/4', '', 2, '<p>Even though we live in a digital world, traditional business marketing tools are still successfully deployed every day in small business marketing. The trick is knowing how to be the most cost effective in using marketing tools such as direct mail, PR, and advertising to generate maximum leads for your dollars invested.</p>\r\n<p>In this Business Accelerator Webinar, Michelle Lanter Smith looks at common non-online lead generation vehicles that yield high returns for the money. Sheâ€™ll disclose some of the tried and true formulas that generate leads that you, as a small business owner, can easily deploy in your marketing plan. Youâ€™ll also learn how to leverage the media to gain exposure and when and where to advertise to generate leads or drive traffic to your door. Hear some helpful tips, as well as things to avoid, when executing these marketing tactics.Â  Finally, youâ€™ll learn how to find the resources you need to deploy a direct mail, PR, or advertising campaign. </p>\r\n', '2012-03-05', '2012-03-26 13:58:29', '', ''),
(26, 'Stir Up the Sales with Online Marketing', 9, 0, 7, '', ' (July 20, 2010 webinar) ', 'https://amfam.webex.com/ec0605lc/eventcenter/recording/recordAction.do?theAction=poprecord&actname=%2Feventcenter%2Fframe%2Fg.do&apiname=lsr.php&renewticket=0&renewticket=0&actappname=ec0605lc&entappname=url0107lc&needFilter=false&&isurlact=true&entactname=%2FnbrRecordingURL.do&rID=39907227&rKey=efe7ce1d46a41770&recordID=39907227&rnd=6179110237&siteurl=amfam&SP=EC&AT=pb&format=short\r\n', '', 4, '<p>Your digital presence is critical for any business operating in todayâ€™s world.Â  In this chapter, our webinar will discuss how you can make your website more than a brochure and how a good website is an essential element in your e-marketing strategy. Weâ€™ll not only discuss design, but components of your site that can make it more interactive and sticky, such as videos, quizzes, and blogs.</p>\r\n<p>Local search is something that small businesses shouldnâ€™t ignore either.Â  In this chapter, we discuss search engine optimization and the difference between paid and organic search.Â  We also explore online advertising and how you advertise on Google, Facebook, and LinkedIn to drive visitors to your site.</p>\r\n<p>Next steps to complete this chapter:</p>\r\n<p>Maximize your SEO: Determine your keywords and then go through your website and make sure you are using them throughout your site.</p>\r\n', '2012-03-05', '2012-03-26 13:46:17', '', ''),
