(29, 'The New E-Billboard for Small Businessâ€”Pay Per Click ', 9, 24, 7, '', '(2012 webinar) ', '/events/view/10', '', 2, '<p>New leads are waiting to be uncovered and in this chapter youâ€™ll learn how to find them with Pay-Per-Click advertising--the new E-Billboard for small business. Pay-Per-Click advertising offers huge benefits over traditional marketing avenues. You can easily control your budget, keeping your costs low.  Also, with PPCâ€™s sophisticated tracking, you can figure out your return on investment with detailed, built-in analytics. </p>\r\n<p>In his webinar, Dean DeLisle explains how to spotlight your business online, drive targeted leads to your website, and improve click-to-close rates through a variety of proven techniques.</p>\r\n', '2012-03-05', '2012-05-24 10:05:18', '', ''),
(30, 'Overview (video) ', 9, 22, 8, '', 'Overview (video) ', 'http://www.kaltura.com/p/737192/sp/73719200/embedIframeJs/uiconf_id/7235092/partner_id/737192', 'http://www.kaltura.com/index.php/kwidget/cache_st/1331330953/wid/_737192/uiconf_id/7235092/entry_id/0_wslnmtqr', 1, '<p>What is marketing?Â  Is it:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>The discipline of selling your product to the customer?</li>\r\n  <li>Selling, the exchange of goods for money and profit?</li>\r\n  <li>A management process through which products move from concept to the customer?</li>\r\n  <li>Building awareness for your company and its products?</li>\r\n  <li>Building positive perceptions for your company and brands?</li>\r\n  <li>Philip Kotlerâ€™s 4Ps?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>In this chapter, Scott Cooper will explore a different way of thinking about marketing.Â  Its focus is external, on the needs and wants of your target audience.Â  This chapter will set the foundation of his approach for his following chapters on Marketing Planning Tips for Small Business.</p>\r\n', '2012-03-05', '2012-03-26 17:46:17', '', ''),
(31, 'Insights (video) ', 9, 22, 8, '', 'Insights (video) ', 'http://www.kaltura.com/p/737192/sp/73719200/embedIframeJs/uiconf_id/7235092/partner_id/737192', 'http://www.kaltura.com/index.php/kwidget/cache_st/1331330551/wid/_737192/uiconf_id/7235092/entry_id/0_nd4fl614', 1, '<p>Let an understanding of your past help show you the future.</p>\r\n<p>In this chapter, Scott Cooper will discuss how important it is to take into account your company history in order to develop your business identity.Â  A good business review provides you with an understanding of your companyâ€™s history.Â  Where youâ€™ve been is often times where youâ€™re goingâ€”understanding the past helps to shape the future.</p>\r\n<p>In addition, Scott will give you a template on how to do a product and sales review. This is key to understanding where you stand in comparison to your competitors and what you may need to do to stay ahead.</p>\r\n', '2012-03-05', '2012-03-26 17:39:19', '', ''),
(32, 'Define Your Targets (video) ', 9, 22, 8, '', 'Define Your Targets (video) ', 'http://www.kaltura.com/p/737192/sp/73719200/embedIframeJs/uiconf_id/7235092/partner_id/737192', 'http://www.kaltura.com/index.php/kwidget/cache_st/1331330853/wid/_737192/uiconf_id/7235092/entry_id/0_zy0wi76h', 1, '<p>If youâ€™re not something special to someone, youâ€™re nothing to everyone.</p>\r\n<p>Defining your target market and honing in the customer you choose to serve is critical to developing your marketing plan and to your future marketing success.Â  In this chapter, Scott Cooper will discuss target market segmentation and why you need to do it.</p>\r\n<p>In addition, Scott will focus on some of the bigger target market questions and give you plenty of ideas on how to get smarter about determining who youâ€™re really forâ€”so you can focus resources on those customers and prospects that matter most.</p>\r\n', '2012-03-05', '2012-03-26 17:45:31', '', ''),
(33, 'Setting Your Objectives (video) ', 9, 22, 8, '', 'Setting Your Objectives (video) ', 'http://www.kaltura.com/p/737192/sp/73719200/embedIframeJs/uiconf_id/7235092/partner_id/737192', 'http://www.kaltura.com/index.php/kwidget/cache_st/1331330759/wid/_737192/uiconf_id/7235092/entry_id/0_z1nincaa', 1, '<p>You canâ€™t manage what you canâ€™t measure!</p>\r\n<p>Often times we set our marketing objectives on metrics that really donâ€™t drive sales. In this chapter, Scott Cooper encourages you to determine your marketing objectives on elements that you can really measure, such as retention, increase usage, new customers. </p>\r\n<p>Scott also explains the connection between marketing objectives and communication objectives.Â  He discusses how communication objectives can be categorized into three areas:Â  awareness, knowledge, attitude and perceptions.</p>\r\n', '2012-03-05', '2012-03-26 17:47:15', '', ''),
(34, 'Positioning (video) ', 9, 22, 8, '', 'Positioning (video) ', 'http://www.kaltura.com/p/737192/sp/73719200/embedIframeJs/uiconf_id/7235092/partner_id/737192', 'http://www.kaltura.com/index.php/kwidget/cache_st/1331330355/wid/_737192/uiconf_id/7235092/entry_id/0_d6c5qi2t', 1, '<p>Positioning is the art of sacrifice.</p>\r\n<p>A companyâ€™s or productâ€™s positioning defines how itâ€™s different to the world.Â  Every company, every product, every person has a brand positioning whether they work at it or not.Â  In this chapter, Scott Cooper takes you through the steps on how to position your company or product.</p>\r\n<p>In addition, Scott gives you some ideas on how to write your positioning statement.</p>\r\n', '2012-03-05', '2012-03-26 17:53:47', '', ''),
(35, 'Positioning Your Business For Success (webinar 2012) ', 9, 22, 8, '', 'Positioning Your Business For Success (webinar 2012) ', '/events/view/3', '', 2, '<p>In this webinar, Scott Cooper discusses how to develop your business'' positioning. We''ll explore the reasons companies spend so much time on this issue and then we''ll jump right into how you''d go about positioning your company by answering three questions:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n  <li>Who are you for?</li>\r\n  <li>What is it you really do for your customers?</li>\r\n  <li>And how are you meaningfully different? \r\n  </li>\r\n</ol>\r\n', '2012-03-05', '2012-05-24 10:05:18', '', ''),
(36, 'Define Your Message (video) ', 9, 22, 8, '', 'Define Your Message (video) ', 'http://www.kaltura.com/p/737192/sp/73719200/embedIframeJs/uiconf_id/7235092/partner_id/737192', 'http://www.kaltura.com/index.php/kwidget/cache_st/1331330420/wid/_737192/uiconf_id/7235092/entry_id/0_g034ghd4', 1, '<p>&ldquo;Advertising messages say to people, here&rsquo;s what we&rsquo;ve got, here&rsquo;s what it will do for you and here&rsquo;s where to get it.&rdquo;Â  <em>Leo Burnett</em></p>\r\n<p>In this chapter, Scott Cooper explains how the positioning statement generates your message strategy.Â  He demonstrates a simple exercise that can help you structure your company&rsquo;s thinking about its communications.Â  This exercise is a creative brief; it can give you the focus and clarity you and your design team needs to create the right execution to foster your company&rsquo;s positioning.</p>\r\n', '2012-03-05', '2012-03-26 17:48:48', '', ''),
(37, 'Set Strategies (video) ', 9, 22, 8, '', 'Set Strategies (video) ', 'http://www.kaltura.com/p/737192/sp/73719200/embedIframeJs/uiconf_id/7235092/partner_id/737192', 'http://www.kaltura.com/index.php/kwidget/cache_st/1331330499/wid/_737192/uiconf_id/7235092/entry_id/0_y1mhm71t', 1, '<p>&ldquo;Order or disorder depends upon organization.&rdquo; <em>Sun Tzu</em></p>\r\n<p>You&rsquo;ve defined your target market, set your objectives, defined your brand positioning and the message that will tell your positioning story, now what are you going to do to accomplish your objectives and tell your story?</p>\r\n<p>In this chapter, Scott Cooper will discuss various marketing strategies that companies can employ to achieve their objectives, such as: low cost, steal share, innovator, and follower.</p>\r\n', '2012-03-05', '2012-03-26 17:47:56', '', ''),
(38, 'Mass Communications (video) ', 9, 22, 8, '', 'Mass Communications (video) ', 'http://www.kaltura.com/p/737192/sp/73719200/embedIframeJs/uiconf_id/7235092/partner_id/737192', 'http://www.kaltura.com/index.php/kwidget/cache_st/1331330160/wid/_737192/uiconf_id/7235092/entry_id/0_nf1kekdu', 1, '<p>&ldquo;Advertising is the wonder in Wonder Bread.&rdquo; <em>Jeff I. Richards</em></p>\r\n<p>All products, no matter how mundane, have a reason for someone to get excited about them.Â  Advertising&rsquo;s job is to find the drama and tell the story so more people hear about it, feel good about it, understand it and talk about it to others.</p>\r\n<p>In this chapter, Scott Coopers discusses advertising concepts that work and how to craft your advertising so it gets heard.Â  He also explains the difference between advertising and promotion.Â  Scott goes into detail about the different promotional categories to consider in your marketing efforts and their associated advantages and disadvantages.Â  This chapter also discusses the benefits and the nuances of PR, mass media, and outdoor advertising.</p>\r\n', '2012-03-05', '2012-03-26 17:52:07', '', ''),
(39, 'Interactive Communications (video) ', 9, 22, 8, '', 'Interactive Communications (video) ', 'http://www.kaltura.com/p/737192/sp/73719200/embedIframeJs/uiconf_id/7235092/partner_id/737192', 'http://www.kaltura.com/index.php/kwidget/cache_st/1331330241/wid/_737192/uiconf_id/7235092/entry_id/0_yorkcyis', 1, '<p>Itâ€™s a new world out there. The communication world is coming to us versus us having to go to it. Mobile marketing, social media, web sites, blogs, ezines, and moreâ€”are you ready to join the conversation?</p>\r\n<p>In this chapter, Scott Copper explains how marketers need to be strategic and understand how consumers want to get their informationâ€”they need to be part of mediums that people are actively seeking and using.</p>\r\n<p>Your interactive communication and e-marketing begin with your website.Â  Scott discusses the keys to building a search engine optimized site and how to design your site so it is easy to navigate. He also gives an introductory look at the most common social media platforms and how to get started.Â  Finally, he discusses mobile marketing and how marketers can leverage smart phones to reach their consumers.</p>\r\n', '2012-03-05', '2012-03-26 17:50:15', '', ''),
(40, 'Customer Relationship Marketing (video) ', 9, 22, 8, '', 'Customer Relationship Marketing (video) ', 'http://www.kaltura.com/p/737192/sp/73719200/embedIframeJs/uiconf_id/7235092/partner_id/737192', 'http://www.kaltura.com/index.php/kwidget/cache_st/1331329998/wid/_737192/uiconf_id/7235092/entry_id/0_5n3oqct2', 1, '<p>&ldquo;Never sell a product or service.Â  Always sell a concept.&rdquo;Â  Joe Sugarman, <em>Advertising Secrets of the Written Word</em></p>\r\n<p>Customer Relationship Marketing, or CRM, started with the prominence of the mail order catalog companies. Today, it&rsquo;s widely used across all types of companies to help them build an understanding of customers&rsquo; buying behaviors, their attitudes and perceptions to create actionable insights that result in increased profitability and customer loyalty.</p>\r\n<p>In this chapter, Scott Cooper discusses the building blocks of CRM, i.e., the database, as well as RFM (recency, frequency, and monetary value).Â  He also reveals 10 suggestions to build better communications one-to-one.</p>\r\n', '2012-03-05', '2012-03-26 17:53:06', '', ''),
(41, 'A Database Made of Gold - Customer Relationship Marketing for the Small Business', 9, 0, 8, '', ' (webinar Sept. 15 2011) ', 'https://amfam.webex.com/ec0605lc/eventcenter/recording/recordAction.do?theAction=poprecord&actname=%2Feventcenter%2Fframe%2Fg.do&apiname=lsr.php&renewticket=0&renewticket=0&actappname=ec0605lc&entappname=url0107lc&needFilter=false&&isurlact=true&entactname=%2FnbrRecordingURL.do&rID=44000032&rKey=673f96ec9d6fb3ed&recordID=44000032&rnd=3675738415&siteurl=amfam&SP=EC&AT=pb&format=short\r\n', '', 4, '<p>Customer Relationship Marketing (CRM) is accomplished through learning about your customers and fostering a two-way conversation: a give-and-take that is inevitable in any lasting relationship.Â  In this chapter, Scott Cooper conducts a webinar on CRM and how the small business can leverage it to help grow their business profitably. </p>\r\n<p>In this webinar, weâ€™ll discuss the basics of CRM, how you can successfully manage your contacts and leads, organize a system to track the lead source, rank your lead sources, use CRM to get sales and marketing on the same page, find the best source for leads, and how you can use CRM to provide insights to product development and operations.Â Â  In addition, weâ€™ll talk about monitoring contacts against customers who purchase more, purchase more frequently and who have purchased most recently. </p>\r\n', '2012-03-05', '2012-03-31 19:23:36', '', ''),
(42, 'Evaluate (video) ', 9, 22, 8, '', 'Evaluate (video) ', 'http://www.kaltura.com/p/737192/sp/73719200/embedIframeJs/uiconf_id/7235092/partner_id/737192', 'http://www.kaltura.com/index.php/kwidget/cache_st/1331330078/wid/_737192/uiconf_id/7235092/entry_id/0_grs6l5jw', 1, '<p>&ldquo;Strive for excellence, not perfection.&rdquo; <em>H. Jackson Brown, Jr.</em></p>\r\n<p>Marketing is all about going in the right direction. You rarely reach perfection, but if you keep going in the right direction long enough, you&rsquo;ll win and win big.</p>\r\n<p>In this chapter, Scott Cooper will explain what he thinks you should track to evaluate the success of your marketing plan.Â  He&rsquo;ll also discuss a simple measurement to help you monitor individual tactical programs.</p>\r\n', '2012-03-05', '2012-03-26 17:51:14', '', ''),
(43, 'The Top Three Sales Secrets Every Small Business Owner Needs to Know ', 9, 23, 9, '', '(2011 Spring Symposium; there are 5 segments: Intro to Sales, Secret 1, Secret 2, Secret 3, and Salesperson''s Pledge) ', 'http://hosted.mediasite.com/mediasite/Viewer/?peid=5669867341ae426abd1ecc69657d0c361d', '', 5, '<p>Are you a serious small business owner with a vision for future success or are you simply dabbling in a hobby? If you want to count yourself among the businesses that really make it, then there are three sales secrets you must embrace in order to thrive in any condition. Whether you are a seasoned sales veteran or the thought of selling makes you cringe â€“ donâ€™t miss this opportunity to learn, or refresh yourself on, the three most critical things you must know about sales to set course for small business success. These are sales tools you donâ€™t want to be without.</p>\r\n<p>In this chapter, Bob Wright delivers a motivating symposium to fire you up and get you selling.Â  Be sure to download the sales worksheet so you can begin tracking your daily selling activity.Â  Once you start making your daily dials, youâ€™re guaranteed to see more activity and more business.</p>\r\n<p>Next steps to complete this chapter:</p>\r\n<p>Set your goal to make a minimum of 4 new dials or LinkedIn connections per day.  Watch how your sales pipeline grows over the next few months!</p>\r\n\r\n', '2012-03-05', '2012-03-29 19:53:58', '', ''),
(44, 'Getting Down to Business - Selling & Essential Daily Activity', 9, 0, 9, '', ' (Teleconference 2, 2009) ', 'http://www.slideshare.net/slideshow/embed_code/1761148', '', 3, '<p>As an entrepreneur, you wear a lot of hats.Â  Countless fires and customer demands get in the way of reaching out to new clients, or even current ones, as you work to grow your business to the next level.Â  In this chapter, Dr. Bob Wright will discuss how you can set up effective disciplines to keep your sales plan moving forward.</p>\r\n<p>Dr. Bob will share with you how to overcome your resistance to selling and reveal the things you do that waste time and avoid selling.Â  Heâ€™ll also give you some clues on how to overcome your buyerâ€™s resistance and explain how you can negotiate a close successfully.Â  In this chapterâ€™s webinar, Dr. Bob will touch on the powers of intentional networking and why you can achieve more just by focusing on the connections of the people you already know.</p>\r\n<p>If you havenâ€™t done so already, be sure to download the sales worksheet to start tracking your sales activity.</p>\r\n<p>Next steps to complete this chapter:</p>\r\n<p>Determine how many new business meetings you want to have each week.Â  Track your progress on your sales worksheet, along with your daily dials and conversations.</p>\r\n', '2012-03-05', '2012-03-31 19:23:13', '', ''),
(45, 'Value Based Relationships and Marketing', 9, 0, 9, '', ' (Teleconference 3, 2009) ', 'http://www.slideshare.net/slideshow/embed_code/1827801', '', 3, '<p>Every exchange comes down to value.Â  When you use your cash to make a purchase, youâ€™re actually signaling that the product or service that youâ€™re buying is equal or greater in value to your cash in hand.Â  As a sales person, you must understand the value that your product or service represents to the buyer.Â  In this chapter, weâ€™ll discuss the concept of value and why itâ€™s different than price.</p>\r\n<p>This chapter will feature a teleconference with Dr. Bob where heâ€™ll disclose the concept of Dynamic Value, a process in which you define variables that distinguish your company in the marketplace and map your company against the competition on those key variables.Â  This establishes the foundations for your unique selling proposition.Â  Dr. Bob will also discuss how to introduce yourself when in the sales mode.Â  In this teleconference, he encourages you to get under your strengths and weaknesses and know your Dynamic Value in order to prepare you for all customer interaction.</p>\r\n<p>This chapter also includes articles from author Bob Burg in which he discusses the dynamic of value and how customers price/value tradeoffs every day.</p>\r\n<p>Next steps to complete this chapter:</p>\r\n<p>Take a look at Chapter 1 in the Marketing Course.Â  Download the SWOT primer; this will help you determine your strengths and weaknesses, a prerequisite to knowing your Dynamic Value.</p>\r\n', '2012-03-05', '2012-03-29 19:54:38', '', '');
