(46, 'What is your Personality Style? Building Rapport by Understanding Yourself and Your Clients', 9, 0, 9, '', ' (May 25, 2010 webinar; start at 53:30) ', 'https://amfam.webex.com/ec0605lc/eventcenter/recording/recordAction.do?theAction=poprecord&actname=%2Feventcenter%2Fframe%2Fg.do&apiname=lsr.php&renewticket=0&renewticket=0&actappname=ec0605lc&entappname=url0107lc&needFilter=false&&isurlact=true&entactname=%2FnbrRecordingURL.do&rID=39424152&rKey=89d56f4ff2f75653&recordID=39424152&rnd=5946265123&siteurl=amfam&SP=EC&AT=pb&format=short\r\n', '', 4, '<p>You can increase your sales quickly through better customer communication and relationship-building. In this chapter, weâ€™ll show you how you can achieve the goals in your sales plan by learning to recognize four distinct personality types and adapting your style to connect better to each of them.Â  <br />\r\n  In this chapter, Dr. Bob Wrightâ€™s webinar will help you: </p>\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>Discover your own personality type attributes and abilities</li>\r\n  <li>Recognize the personality type of your customers, suppliers and employees</li>\r\n  <li>Digest and filter information that naturally differs from your point of view</li>\r\n  <li>Improve your listening, communications and rapport building skills to connect better and sell more</li>\r\n  <li>Communicate more effectively and motivate the people you work with on a daily basis</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Prior to diving into this chapter and viewing the webinar, be sure to download Dr. Bobâ€™s C.A.R.E. profile.Â  Take the quiz.Â  The results of the profile will tell you your personality type and will make this chapter much more meaningful for you.<br />\r\n  Next steps to complete this chapter:</p>\r\n<p>Ask your team members to take the C.A.R.E. profile so you can better understand the nuances of how your team interacts and thrives.</p>\r\n', '2012-03-05', '2012-03-29 19:55:01', '', ''),
(47, 'The Five Laws of Stratospheric Success with Bob Burg', 9, 39, 9, '', 'Featured Expert: Bob Burg podcast ', 'http://www.kaltura.com/index.php/kwidget/cache_st/1333032973/wid/_737192/uiconf_id/7642702/entry_id/1_uhrslv57', 'http://www.kaltura.com/index.php/kwidget/cache_st/1333032973/wid/_737192/uiconf_id/7642702/entry_id/1_uhrslv57', 6, '<p>Bob Burg is the bestselling author of <em>Endless Referrals, The Go-Giver</em>, and <em>Go-Givers Sell More</em>.Â  In this exclusive interview, Bob speaks about &ldquo;giving&rdquo; in terms of &ldquo;constantly and consistently adding value to the lives of others.&rdquo; When you can take your focus off yourself and shift it onto how you can be an asset of value to other people, you&rsquo;ll plant seeds of goodwill â€” of great will â€” that will come back to you many, many times over. And not because of some magical, mystical type of thinking, but because it makes absolutely practical sense.</p>\r\n<p>Listen to Bob&rsquo;s podcast with Business Accelerator Host, Euan Ford, to learn more about the First Law: The Law of Value.Â  </p>\r\n<p>Next steps to complete this chapter:</p>\r\n<p>Reflect on the value that you delivered to each of the people you came into contact today.</p>\r\n', '2012-03-05', '2012-03-29 16:23:01', '', ''),
(48, 'Managing the Buying Process: Where are you losing the deal? ', 9, 0, 11, '', '(Core 1 Webinar, June 2, 2011; start at 48:38) ', 'https://amfam.webex.com/ec0605lc/eventcenter/recording/recordAction.do?theAction=poprecord&actname=%2Feventcenter%2Fframe%2Fg.do&apiname=lsr.php&renewticket=0&renewticket=0&actappname=ec0605lc&entappname=url0107lc&needFilter=false&&isurlact=true&entactname=%2FnbrRecordingURL.do&rID=42939477&rKey=993ebce29dc462c4&recordID=42939477&rnd=5918715904&siteurl=amfam&SP=EC&AT=pb&format=short\r\n', '', 4, '<p>Do you understand the different roles and functions involved in the buying process for each of your customers? Do you understand the steps or process for your buyer and yourself in setting up and closing a deal? If not, you are likely leaving money on the table. Increase your awareness and set up your sales system to win a deal, not just sell.</p>\r\n<p>Listen to Dr. Bob Wright explore the buying process and the potential traps where things can go wrong.Â  You can also read Dr. Bob&rsquo;s articles on how to use agendas to ensure that your meeting objectives are met, how to maintain a positive attitude, and how to &ldquo;go for the no.&rdquo;Â  </p>\r\n<p>Next steps to complete this chapter:</p>\r\n<p>Do you have a customer meeting tomorrow? Use one of the sales techniques you learned in this chapter to win the deal.</p>\r\n', '2012-03-05', '2012-03-29 19:55:57', '', ''),
(49, 'The Art and Science of the Sales Call ', 9, 0, 11, '', '(Core Webinar 2: June 16,2011, start at 40:16) ', 'https://amfam.webex.com/ec0605lc/eventcenter/recording/recordAction.do?theAction=poprecord&actname=%2Feventcenter%2Fframe%2Fg.do&apiname=lsr.php&renewticket=0&renewticket=0&actappname=ec0605lc&entappname=url0107lc&needFilter=false&&isurlact=true&entactname=%2FnbrRecordingURL.do&rID=43069747&rKey=b32b9d0a89b7fd5b&recordID=43069747&rnd=6676329818&siteurl=amfam&SP=EC&AT=pb&format=short\r\n', '', 4, '<p>Successful salespeople embrace both the art and the science of the sales call. They prepare and follow the basic steps of the sales process, but they also embrace the art of the sales call by learning to develop themselves fully. Sales success doesn''t just mean asking for the deal. It means building a relationship by being curious, learning to create meaningful conversations with your potential buyers, and adding value in every interaction. </p>\r\n<p>In this chapter, Dr. Bob Wright will explore the various components of the sales call, helping you understand where you can succeed and where you can fail.  Included in this chapter are articles that dive into specifics that everyone tackles in a sales call, such as:  getting past the gatekeeper, handling objections and facing rejection. These are sales techniques developed to help you win the deal.</p>\r\n<p>Next steps to complete this chapter:</p>\r\n<p>At your next sales call, listen for an objection.  Use the steps discussed in this chapter to tackle it head-on.</p>\r\n', '2012-03-05', '2012-03-29 19:58:25', '', ''),
(50, 'Overcoming Objections by Understanding Yourself ', 9, 0, 11, '', '(June 22, 2010 webinar; start at 1 hr 18 min) ', 'https://amfam.webex.com/ec0605lc/eventcenter/recording/recordAction.do?theAction=poprecord&actname=%2Feventcenter%2Fframe%2Fg.do&apiname=lsr.php&renewticket=0&renewticket=0&actappname=ec0605lc&entappname=url0107lc&needFilter=false&&isurlact=true&entactname=%2FnbrRecordingURL.do&rID=39685142&rKey=646f636b676656f4&recordID=39685142&rnd=8920628540&siteurl=amfam&SP=EC&AT=pb&format=short\r\n', '', 4, '<p>We know theyâ€™re coming.Â  Every customer usually has at least one or two.Â  Objections, that is.</p>\r\n<p>In this chapter, we explore the catalysts behind objectionsâ€”not only of your customers but of your own resistance to face them.Â  In his webinar, Dr. Bob Wright will discuss how objections are really valuable data about our prospects and customers; objections will help us understand what it will take to win their business.</p>\r\n<p>Dr. Bob will also talk about resistance and the various categories of resistance that youâ€™ll face on a sales call.Â  Going deeper, though, heâ€™ll explore how your customerâ€™s personality type will determine how their resistance is manifested.Â  By knowing your personality type, you understand better how you deal with the resistanceâ€”do you shrink or do you overcome?</p>\r\n<p>Next steps to complete this chapter:</p>\r\n<p>At your next sales meeting, ask a customer what it will take to win the business.Â </p>\r\n', '2012-03-05', '2012-03-29 19:59:05', '', ''),
(51, 'Winning Sales Negotiations (2012 webinar) ', 9, 23, 11, '', 'Winning Sales Negotiations (2012 webinar) ', '/events/view/7', '', 2, '<p>Many of us approach sales negotiations with a win/lose mindset. However, sales negotiations that create lasting relationships and repeat buyers are never born of this approach. Successful sales negotiations create win/win results where everyone comes out satisfied with the value they have received for their investment. But what does this look like in practice? How can you win sales negotiations while winning in relationship? </p>\r\n<p>In this webinar, Dr. Bob Wright teaches how to approach a sales negotiation and how to have everyone walking away winning.</p>\r\n', '2012-03-05', '2012-03-26 14:46:12', '', ''),
(52, 'Mastering the Complex Sale (2012 webinar) ', 9, 23, 11, '', 'Mastering the Complex Sale (2012 webinar) ', '/events/view/12', '', 2, '<p>As an entrepreneur, we rarely take the time to analyze the sales process for a particular prospect or customer.Â  Too often, we remain short-sighted when we are making the sale and we donâ€™t land the deal because of its complexity.</p>\r\n<p>In this chapter, Dr. Bob Wright will explore the many facets of a complex saleâ€”including whatâ€™s really going on behind the scene. Youâ€™ll discover that you are always selling to a team even when there is only one individual across from you. Youâ€™ll come away with sales techniques to better identify the key players of the sale and gain sales strategies into how to understand the components of a sale to better ensure successful outcomes.</p>\r\n', '2012-03-05', '2012-03-26 14:47:29', '', ''),
(53, 'Four Steps to a High Impact Elevator Pitch ', 9, 0, 12, '', '(June 8, 2010 webinar; start at beginning) ', 'https://amfam.webex.com/ec0605lc/eventcenter/recording/recordAction.do?theAction=poprecord&actname=%2Feventcenter%2Fframe%2Fg.do&apiname=lsr.php&renewticket=0&renewticket=0&actappname=ec0605lc&entappname=url0107lc&needFilter=false&&isurlact=true&entactname=%2FnbrRecordingURL.do&rID=39551827&rKey=391bb166659c8b05&recordID=39551827&rnd=4624955574&siteurl=amfam&SP=EC&AT=pb&format=short\r\n', '', 4, '<p>You only have 30 seconds to gain someoneâ€™s interest in what you do.Â  Sometimes less! But how do you know what people want to know about you?Â  How do you take everything that you have to offer and shrink it down to only 30-seconds?</p>\r\n<p>In this chapter, Barbara Lopez will teach you her F.A.R.M. systemâ€”an easy template to building your elevator introduction.Â  Learn how to craft your introduction so you stand out from others, your business identity shines through and you keep them coming back for more.</p>\r\n<p>Be sure to download the handout while you listen to the webinar.Â  You can get started on crafting your introduction right away.</p>\r\n<p>Next steps to complete this chapter:</p>\r\n<p>Post your elevator introduction on the Business Accelerator LinkedIn discussion group.Â  Try it out on some of your fellow Business Accelerator members.</p>\r\n', '2012-03-05', '2012-03-29 19:59:35', '', ''),
(54, 'Networking How-To''s for Those Who Hate to Network', 9, 0, 12, '', ' (Nov 10, 2011 webinar) ', 'https://amfam.webex.com/ec0605lc/eventcenter/recording/recordAction.do?theAction=poprecord&actname=%2Feventcenter%2Fframe%2Fg.do&apiname=lsr.php&renewticket=0&renewticket=0&actappname=ec0605lc&entappname=url0107lc&needFilter=false&&isurlact=true&entactname=%2FnbrRecordingURL.do&rID=44688487&rKey=28ca4275e8a5a2b5&recordID=44688487&rnd=9967279089&siteurl=amfam&SP=EC&AT=pb&format=short\r\n', '', 4, '<p>Networking is about contactâ€”contact with people.Â  But what if you donâ€™t like to make contact with people, particularly strangers, on a regular basis?Â  Does this sound like the scream of the inner demons inside your head?Â  Â Well, networking is a primary sales tool for those who drive revenue, and networking is a skill set well worth developing.Â  In fact, itâ€™s a necessity.Â  </p>\r\n<p>In this chapter, Barbara Lopez gives you words to use to help start conversations, probe to learn more about someone, communicate your value, and exit the conversation gracefully.Â  Sheâ€™ll also discuss how to prepare both mentally and physically for the event; and, sheâ€™ll cover the steps you must take after the networking event to ensure you take your new connections to the next step.</p>\r\n<p>Next steps to complete this chapter:</p>\r\n<p>Plan to arrive at your next networking event 15 minutes before the start time so you can welcome people to the event.</p>\r\n', '2012-03-05', '2012-03-29 20:00:12', '', ''),
(55, 'Referrals: A Gift that Keeps on Giving ', 9, 0, 12, '', '(Core Webinar 4, July 4, 2011; start at 1 hour 2 mins) ', 'https://amfam.webex.com/ec0605lc/eventcenter/recording/recordAction.do?theAction=poprecord&actname=%2Feventcenter%2Fframe%2Fg.do&apiname=lsr.php&renewticket=0&renewticket=0&actappname=ec0605lc&entappname=url0107lc&needFilter=false&&isurlact=true&entactname=%2FnbrRecordingURL.do&rID=43331272&rKey=36b8513f3a4a5a73&recordID=43331272&rnd=3007574920&siteurl=amfam&SP=EC&AT=pb&format=short\r\n', '', 4, '<p>Your next customer is right under your nose, but do you have a plan to get introduced? Referrals can be one of the most potent sources for lead generation that you have at your disposal. Referrals offer you qualified leads, with a far higher return on your sales investment than many other lead generation opportunities. And yet most sales people treat them as a bonus when they come along rather than setting up their sales calls to generate referrals. </p>\r\n<p>In this chapter, discover whatâ€™s in the way of your referral generating success and set up a system that will keep putting new resources right in your pocket and pipeline!Â  Be sure to read the articles included in this chapter too; find out how a simple thank you can go a long way.</p>\r\n<p>Next steps to complete this chapter:</p>\r\n<p>Donâ€™t forget to ask! Track how many times you asked for a referral this week.</p>\r\n', '2012-03-05', '2012-03-29 20:00:59', '', ''),
(56, 'Where are your Leads Coming From? How to Leverage Lead Generation for Maxium Return ', 9, 0, 12, '', '(May 11, 2010 webinar; start at 5:56) ', 'https://amfam.webex.com/ec0605lc/eventcenter/recording/recordAction.do?theAction=poprecord&actname=%2Feventcenter%2Fframe%2Fg.do&apiname=lsr.php&renewticket=0&renewticket=0&actappname=ec0605lc&entappname=url0107lc&needFilter=false&&isurlact=true&entactname=%2FnbrRecordingURL.do&rID=39286687&rKey=95445329a5473c4e&recordID=39286687&rnd=6551510633&siteurl=amfam&SP=EC&AT=pb&format=short\r\n', '', 4, '<p>Lead generation can be a daunting task.Â  Even more, determining which lead generation engine is working the best can be even harder.Â  In this chapter, Dr. Bob Wright explains a methodology that you can use to evaluate your lead generation.Â  Heâ€™ll explore important questions such as: Is your lead generation not up to par because you havenâ€™t focused on the area?Â  Might you need to shift how you are approaching that area of the business? Do you need to consider letting go of it all together and assigning it to someone else?</p>\r\n<p>In addition to the webinar, this chapter includes some key articles to get your thoughts engaged on how to generate leads.</p>\r\n', '2012-03-05', '2012-03-29 20:03:12', '', ''),
(57, 'Make More Money By Managing Your Business, Part I: Intro to Finance', 9, 0, 13, '', ' Intro to Finance', 'http://hosted.mediasite.com/mediasite/Viewer/?peid=b3f9bf21307a4aeb85e8860705dc88291d', '', 5, '<p>Is your business thriving or barely surviving? If you want to make more money, then you must commit to managing your business. But what does that really mean? Too often, as small business owners you focus on what you know best. Perhaps youâ€™re a technician in your field so you get overly involved in the next technological advance while neglecting your basic budgeting. Or if you love to market, you may consume yourself with your website and marketing materials but not have a perspective on your businessâ€™ profitability. </p>\r\n<p>In this chapter, weâ€™ll talk about the inâ€™s and outâ€™s of understanding and interpreting financial results for better management decisions for small businesses.Â  No matter what your background or goals, whether you are just starting out or simply refining your business model, make sure youâ€™re putting the basics to work for you. </p>\r\n<p>Next steps to complete this chapter:</p>\r\n<p>Pull your profit &amp; loss statement for the month and compare it to last yearâ€™s.Â  Are you ahead, on track or behind?Â  What decisions should be made now to ensure better profitability at the end of the year?</p>\r\n', '2012-03-05', '2012-03-29 20:07:46', '', ''),
(58, 'Improving Your Cash Flow with Barbara Weltman ', 9, 0, 13, '', 'Improving Your Cash Flow with Barbara Weltman ', 'http://www.kaltura.com/p/737192/sp/73719200/embedIframeJs/uiconf_id/7235092/partner_id/737192', 'http://www.kaltura.com/index.php/kwidget/cache_st/1331331065/wid/_737192/uiconf_id/7235092/entry_id/0_hzqs7cex', 1, ' ', '2012-03-05', '2012-05-24 10:05:18', '', ''),
(59, 'Financing Your Business ', 9, 0, 13, '', '(Core Webinar 2: June 30,2011, start at 1:50) ', 'https://amfam.webex.com/ec0605lc/eventcenter/recording/recordAction.do?theAction=poprecord&actname=%2Feventcenter%2Fframe%2Fg.do&apiname=lsr.php&renewticket=0&renewticket=0&actappname=ec0605lc&entappname=url0107lc&needFilter=false&&isurlact=true&entactname=%2FnbrRecordingURL.do&rID=43069747&rKey=b32b9d0a89b7fd5b&recordID=43069747&rnd=6676329818&siteurl=amfam&SP=EC&AT=pb&format=short\r\n', '', 4, '<p>Whatâ€™s available to you as a small business owner if youâ€™re in need of funds?Â  You hear about lines of credit, credit cards, small business loansâ€”but which of them make sense and which of them can get you into big trouble?Â  </p>\r\n<p>Financing a small business can be confusing and overwhelming at best.Â  In this chapter, our webinar will explore the various types of financing that are available to small business owners.Â  We explore topics such as when do you look for financing and when do you go it on your own?Â  Finally, weâ€™ll explore several small business scenarios that can give you some insight into what you need to know to keep your business afloat.</p>\r\n<p>Next steps to complete this chapter:</p>\r\n<p>Look at your profit &amp; loss statement and consider whether additional financing is necessaryâ€”and viable.</p>\r\n', '2012-03-05', '2012-03-26 13:52:01', '', ''),
(60, 'Managing Risk in Your Business ', 9, 0, 13, '', '(June 1, 2010 webinar) ', 'https://amfam.webex.com/ec0605lc/eventcenter/recording/recordAction.do?theAction=poprecord&actname=%2Feventcenter%2Fframe%2Fg.do&apiname=lsr.php&renewticket=0&renewticket=0&actappname=ec0605lc&entappname=url0107lc&needFilter=false&&isurlact=true&entactname=%2FnbrRecordingURL.do&rID=39481462&rKey=50bace3ea4676de0&recordID=39481462&rnd=0.92808813839916&siteurl=amfam&SP=EC&AT=pb&format=short\r\n', '', 4, '<p>Risk is all around you.Â  You face it every day in your business.Â  Risk of not making the sale.Â  Risk of losing a customer.Â  But do you think of the risk you bear of losing your business to disaster or errors?</p>\r\n<p>In this chapter, Trinidad Perez and Mondale Smith of American Family Insurance, talk about the proactive steps you can take to reduce your business risk.Â  Theyâ€™ll also discuss the types of insurance coverage available to reduce your risk and how to select an insurance agent or broker to guide you through these important business decisions.</p>\r\n<p>Be sure to download all chapters of the <em>Open for Business</em> Risk Assessment Tool.Â  This tool will provide you a template that you can complete which will help you prepare your business for unexpected disasters.</p>\r\n<p>Next steps to complete this chapter:</p>\r\n<p>Before going through the Risk Assessment Tool, do an inventory of the different insurance coverage you currently have.</p>\r\n', '2012-03-05', '2012-03-26 13:52:26', '', ''),
(61, 'Power Up Your Productivity ', 9, 0, 14, '', '(Feb. 24, 2011 webinar) ', 'https://amfam.webex.com/ec0605lc/eventcenter/recording/recordAction.do?theAction=poprecord&actname=%2Feventcenter%2Fframe%2Fg.do&apiname=lsr.php&renewticket=0&renewticket=0&actappname=ec0605lc&entappname=url0107lc&needFilter=false&&isurlact=true&entactname=%2FnbrRecordingURL.do&rID=41930942&rKey=fc710eb6b932c887&recordID=41930942&rnd=2256454977&siteurl=amfam&SP=EC&AT=pb&format=short\r\n', '', 4, '<p>Do you often hear people complain about how busy they are?Â  Are they really busy or are they really just overstressed from information overload: too cluttered to see tasks at hand clearly; too overwhelmed to see how they can manage their work more productively?</p>\r\n<p>In this chapter, weâ€™ll hear Leslie Shreve present simple secrets to save time, stay in control and feel fantastic in your work day. Â Â The cost of disorganization to you and your company can be huge.Â  In this chapter youâ€™ll learn some steps to getting and staying organized.Â  Leslie will also discuss three ways to protect your time.</p>\r\n<p>Take some time to read Leslieâ€™s articles included in this chapter.Â  If you take the initiative to implement just a few of her time-saving and organizational days, youâ€™ll be sure to have many productive days ahead.</p>\r\n<p>Next steps to complete this chapter:</p>\r\n<p>Through your post-it notes away!Â  Turn to your task list in Outlook or some other electronic organizer.</p>\r\n', '2012-03-05', '2012-03-29 20:11:55', '', ''),
(62, 'Featured Expert - Turbo Charge Your Task List with Leslie Shreve ', 9, 41, 14, '', 'Featured Expert - Turbo Charge Your Task List with Leslie Shreve ', 'http://www.kaltura.com/index.php/kwidget/cache_st/1333032933/wid/_737192/uiconf_id/7642702/entry_id/1_tjv7q1bz', 'http://www.kaltura.com/index.php/kwidget/cache_st/1333032933/wid/_737192/uiconf_id/7642702/entry_id/1_tjv7q1bz', 6, '<p>Are you feeling completely overwhelmed with everything on your &ldquo;work day plate?&rdquo; Are you ready to be more proactive and productive instead of <em>busy</em> being reactive?</p>\r\n<p>In this chapter, productivity coach Leslie Shreve will discuss on her podcast her break-through approached, called Taskologyâ„¢--the science of getting things done.Â  She&rsquo;ll discuss why paper is never going to be enough to control your task list and the benefits of trying her approach.Â  Leslie will also give you tips on how to get started in your office with finding all your tasks.</p>\r\n<p>Be sure to read Leslie&rsquo;s articles included in this chapter for more insight on how to improve your daily productivity and get more clarity and control back into your workday.</p>\r\n<p>Next steps to complete this chapter:</p>\r\n<p>Instead of pulling jotting action items on post-it notes, use the Task List in Microsoft Outlook or a similar calendar application.</p>\r\n', '2012-03-05', '2012-03-31 19:22:48', '', ''),
(63, 'Protect Your Business: Risk Management, Disaster Protection and Recovery', 9, 0, 14, '', ' (2011 webinar) ', 'https://amfam.webex.com/ec0605lc/eventcenter/recording/recordAction.do?theAction=poprecord&actname=%2Feventcenter%2Fframe%2Fg.do&apiname=lsr.php&renewticket=0&renewticket=0&actappname=ec0605lc&entappname=url0107lc&needFilter=false&&isurlact=true&entactname=%2FnbrRecordingURL.do&rID=44946812&rKey=188c515906d87b78&recordID=44946812&rnd=2713674622&siteurl=amfam&SP=EC&AT=pb&format=short\r\n', '', 4, '<p>Protecting your business in case of unforeseen disasters, theft, or even damaging errors is something all business owners face, but often ignore.Â  This chapter will inform you of the risks that are out there and what you can do to protect your business to minimize your risk.Â  </p>\r\n<p>In the webinar, Trinidad Perez of American Family Insurance, talks about the proactive steps you can take to reduce your business risk.Â  Sheâ€™ll also discuss how you can protect your business from disasters and how you can ensure that youâ€™ll be up and running as soon as possible after a disaster.Â  </p>\r\n<p>Be sure to download all chapters of the <em>Open for Business</em> Risk Assessment Tool.Â  This tool will provide you a template that you can complete which will help you prepare your business for unexpected disasters.</p>\r\n<p>Next steps to complete this chapter:</p>\r\n<p>Before going through the Risk Assessment Tool, do an inventory of the different insurance coverage you currently have.</p>\r\n', '2012-03-05', '2012-03-26 13:53:17', '', ''),
(64, 'Managing Your Most Important Asset: HR Topics for the Small Business', 9, 0, 14, '', 'HR Topics for the Small Business (Aug 24, 2010 webinar) ', 'https://amfam.webex.com/ec0605lc/eventcenter/recording/recordAction.do?theAction=poprecord&actname=%2Feventcenter%2Fframe%2Fg.do&apiname=lsr.php&renewticket=0&renewticket=0&actappname=ec0605lc&entappname=url0107lc&needFilter=false&&isurlact=true&entactname=%2FnbrRecordingURL.do&rID=40194532&rKey=2955b65395864333&recordID=40194532&rnd=6739656493&siteurl=amfam&SP=EC&AT=pb&format=short\r\n', '', 4, '<p>In a small business, you know what they say, &ldquo;slow to hire, fast to fire.&rdquo;Â  Your staff can make or break your business, so choosing your employees and determining how to compensate and motivate them is critical.</p>\r\n<p>In this chapter, Michelle Binks&rsquo; webinar will explore some of the hiring pitfalls that many small business owners face, as well as compensation and vacation topics. She&rsquo;ll look at the pros and cons of hiring contractors versus employees and she&rsquo;ll discuss how to hire and fire within the law.Â  Michelle will also talk about the very important employee handbook, as well as items that you do and do not want to keep in an employee&rsquo;s file.Â  Finally, Michelle also offers some very helpful websites and resources so you can attempt to comply with Federal employment laws.Â  </p>\r\n<p>In addition, we&rsquo;ll also explore how to deal with the &lsquo;hard to handle&rsquo; employee in this chapter and Michael Hahn will discuss how to motivate your team to peak performance in the webinar. </p>\r\n<p>Next steps to complete this chapter:</p>\r\n<p>Go through your employee files to see if you are holding onto the right items.</p>\r\n', '2012-03-05', '2012-03-29 20:12:40', '', ''),
(65, 'Systemizing Your Activity for Growth: The Why, What, and How of Systems ', 9, 0, 14, '', '(Sept 19, 2009 slideshare) ', 'http://www.slideshare.net/slideshow/embed_code/2034052', '', 3, '<p>Your business is built on systems:Â  accounting, order entry, customer service, in-bound mail.Â  Systems are a series or network of processes, actions, or functions that generally have an input or output and a process in between. Systems are key to your future business growth.</p>\r\n<p>In this chapter Dr. Bob Wright and Rich Lyons will review the evolution of systems as businesses develop.Â  Theyâ€™ll also explore how systems are built and how they are maintained.Â  Most importantly, theyâ€™ll discuss how you go about improving your systemsâ€”a necessary step prior to major growth of your company.</p>\r\n<p>Next steps to complete this chapter:</p>\r\n<p>Create an inventory of all the processes you currently have within your business and evaluate their efficacy.</p>\r\n', '2012-03-05', '2012-03-29 20:13:22', '', ''),
(66, 'Project Planning for the Small Business Owner ', 9, 0, 14, '', '(2012 webinar) ', '/events/view/8', '', 2, '<p>In this webinar, youâ€™ll learn the doâ€™s and donâ€™ts of managing a project, taught by certified program manager trainer Dana Brownlee, yet tailored to the project management needs of small business owners. Sheâ€™ll cover how to:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>Use key initiating questions for optimal project selection</li>\r\n  <li>Develop a project charter to ensure that everyone is &quot;on the same page&quot; before the project begins</li>\r\n  <li>Implement a four step process to develop a realistic project schedule used to manage key tasks and milestones</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Include a broad array of materials in your project plan</p>\r\n', '2012-03-05', '2012-05-24 10:05:18', '', ''),
