(7, 'Winning Sales Negotiations', 'Winning Sales Negotiations', '2012-06-21 11:00:00', '2032-01-01 00:00:00', 'MST', 0, '&lt;p&gt;Many of us approach sales negotiations with a win/lose mindset. However, sales negotiations that create lasting relationships and repeat buyers are never born of this approach. Successful sales negotiations create win/win results where everyone comes out satisfied with the value they have received for their investment. But what does this look like in practice? How can you win sales negotiations while winning in relationship? Dr. Bob Wright teaches how to approach a sales negotiation and how to have everyone walking away winning.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;If your sales and marketing plan depends on developing client relationships and closing sales, don&amp;rsquo;t miss this Business Accelerator Webinar.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Dr. Robert Wright is an internationally recognized and cutting-edge author, speaker, program developer, CEO coach, and highly successful entrepreneur. Considered one of the nation&amp;rsquo;s leading thinkers in human development and recognized by Crain&amp;rsquo;s Chicago Business as a top executive coach, Dr. Wright specializes in helping corporate leaders and entrepreneurs across the country not only to build and grow their businesses, but also to thrive with purpose, mission, and robust, high-performing cultures. He is the author of &lt;em&gt;Beyond Time Management: Business with Purpose&lt;/em&gt; and the co-founder of the Wright Business Institute in Chicago, helping leaders, entrepreneurs, families, individuals, and organizations realize their fullest potential in all areas of life. In his most recent venture, he co-founded and serves as CEO and faculty of the Wright Graduate Institute for the Realization of Human Potential, a graduate school offering masters and doctoral degrees in human development.&lt;/p&gt;', 'Successful sales negotiations create win/win results where everyone comes out satisfied.', '//c9890511.