(11, 'Managing Your Financial Score Card', '', '2012-10-11 11:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'CST', 1, '<p>As a small business owner, being able to understand and interpret your financial results is imperative for making better management decisions.  Few entrepreneurs fully understand the meaning behind financial statements or know how their businesses are <em>truly</em> doing.  But those who <em>do,</em> hold the power. </p>\r\n<p>When complete and well prepared, financial statements contain an incredible amount of timely and revealing information about a businessâ€™ financial health: its strengths, vulnerabilities and challenges . . . whether or not itâ€™s on track . . . or if itâ€™s really making money. </p>\r\n<p>In this Business Accelerator Webinar, youâ€™ll learn how to:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>Understand your key financial statements and quickly zero in on the most important numbers</li>\r\n  <li>Detect variances while thereâ€™s still time to take corrective action</li>\r\n  <li>Appreciate key financial analysis ratios and tools</li>\r\n  <li>Get a firm grip on your companyâ€™s lifebloodâ€”cash flow</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>This webinar will be led by Lee Werner, a thirty-year accounting professional overseeing accounting and financial operations for both manufacturing and not-for-profit organizations.  Lee has a passion to help business owners take their businesses to a higher level of profitability by finding ways to increase revenues, reducing operational costs and increasing effectiveness. Lee has accomplished this through coaching, training, and supervising both entry-level accounting and bookkeeping staff as well as corporate and C-Suite Executive level staff and board members. Lee has gone beyond our U.S. border and used his business experience by training small business owners and entrepreneurs in Haiti and Kenya over the last several years. Additionally, he facilitates small group coaching sessions for Chicago-area insurance professionals and is an instructor and faculty advisor in accounting and recordkeeping at a local business school for entrepreneurs.</p>\r\n', '', '//c9890511.ssl.cf2.rackcdn.com/71333335481.jpg', 'Lee Werner', 3, 1, 0, '', '', '', '', '2012-03-08 16:47:34', '2012-06-04 12:30:35'),
(12, 'Mastering the Complex Sale', '', '2012-11-08 11:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'CST', 1, '<p>As an entrepreneur, we rarely take the time to analyze the sales process for a particular prospect or customer.  Too often, we remain short-sighted when we are making the sale and we donâ€™t land the deal because of its complexity.</p>\r\n<p>One mistake than many of us make is that we take everything for face value.  In <em>Mastering the Complex Sale</em>, Dr. Bob Wright will explore the many facets of a complex saleâ€”including whatâ€™s really going on behind the scene. Youâ€™ll discover that you are always selling to a team even when there is only one individual across from you. Youâ€™ll find ways to better identify the key players of the sale and gain strategies into how to understand the components of a sale to better ensure successful outcomes.</p>\r\n<p>If your sales and marketing plan depends on mastering the art of closing complex sales, donâ€™t miss this Business Accelerator Webinar.</p>\r\n<p>Dr. Robert Wright is an internationally recognized and cutting-edge author, speaker, program developer, CEO coach, and highly successful entrepreneur. Considered one of the nationâ€™s leading thinkers in human development and recognized by Crainâ€™s Chicago Business as a top executive coach, Dr. Wright specializes in helping corporate leaders and entrepreneurs across the country not only to build and grow their businesses, but also to thrive with purpose, mission, and robust, high-performing cultures. He is the author of <em>Beyond Time Management: Business with Purpose</em> and the co-founder of the Wright Business Institute in Chicago, helping leaders, entrepreneurs, families, individuals, and organizations realize their fullest potential in all areas of life. In his most recent venture, he co-founded and serves as CEO and faculty of the Wright Graduate Institute for the Realization of Human Potential, a graduate school offering masters and doctoral degrees in human development.</p>\r\n', '', '//c9890511.ssl.cf2.rackcdn.com/71333335570.jpg', 'Dr. Bob Wright', 3, 1, 0, '', '', '', '', '2012-03-08 16:49:00', '2012-06-04 12:30:35'),
(13, 'Protect Your Business Life', '', '2012-12-06 11:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'CST', 1, '<p>As an entrepreneur, we rarely take the time to analyze or think about how Life Insurance can help protect the dreams we have worked so hard to create â€“ our businesses.</p>\r\n<p>Join this webinar to learn all about how what you need to be aware of, why you should consider life insurance and what you may be exposed to as a result of not having enough or adequate coverage. </p>\r\n<p>Carl Ivey is a Life Insurance consultant with American Family Insurance and works with business owners to make sure they understand their risks, the protection they should consider and then works to identify suitable solutions for their needs. Benefit from Carlâ€™s over 20 years of experience in making sure business owners have adequate protection should the unfortunate unforeseen circumstances arise. </p>\r\n', '', '//c9890511.ssl.cf2.rackcdn.com/71333377045.jpg', 'Carl Ivey', 3, 1, 0, '', '', '', '', '2012-03-08 16:50:02', '2012-04-03 12:17:23'),
(14, 'Turbo Charge Your Network for Extraordinary Growth - The Business Accelerator Boot Camp', '', '2012-06-07 08:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'CST', 1, '<p>Are you ready to accelerate your business?  Does your sales and marketing plan require that you see results fairly quickly but you arenâ€™t quite sure how to generate the leads to grow your revenue?  Join us at the Business Accelerator Boot Camp where youâ€™ll build a results-focused action plan that will turbo charge your sales in the next six months by leveraging your current network.  </p>\r\n<p>Business opportunities lie dormant, just waiting for you to uncover them. With limited financial resources, it can be difficult to find them with traditional lead generation tools.  Fortunately, you have the power within your own network to boost your business to its next level. Learn how to leverage your current network and revitalize your dormant contacts.  Learn how to use social media to build your network by millions in minutes. Learn how to break down the barriers that stop you from discovering connections with people that are your ticket to a huge sale.  </p>\r\n<p>In this Business Accelerator Boot Camp, weâ€™ll teach you how to sell more in the normal course of your business day with more focused effort, but with minimal time requirement.</p>\r\n', '', '//c9890511.ssl.cf2.rackcdn.com/71333376896.jpg', '', 4, 1, 0, '', '', '', '', '2012-03-08 16:51:07', '2012-06-04 12:26:25'),
(15, 'Making Time for Selling with Roula Crews', '', '2012-04-13 11:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'CST', 1, '<p>As small  business owners, we all wear a lot of hats and one of the most important ones  is that of Sales. Yet, itâ€™s a proven fact that many entrepreneurs donâ€™t make  selling one of their priorities.  </p>\r\n<p>So whatâ€™s  stopping you? Too many other responsibilities? Fear? When a day goes by and you  realize you never made one sales call, what was it that got in your way?</p>\r\n<p>More  important than what stopped you, though, is how to prevent it from stopping you  in the future.</p>\r\n<p>If you need help  moving your sales efforts to the front burner, then join Roula Crews, a  professional sales coach, for this Sales Coach Chat. Tell her what you think is  getting in your way and get her advice on changes you can make. Come prepared  with your questions on what you can do to Make Time for Selling.</p>\r\n<p>Roula Crews is a founding partner  of Hi-Impact Marketing &amp; Sales Solutions, Inc. and has played a key role in  the growth of the Business Accelerator Program through her of her ability to connect and partner with  local and national multicultural chambers. Through her  one-on-one sales training and coaching, sheâ€™s helped clients increase their  sales by as much as 20%.  With over  twenty years of sales experience, Roula loves aiming high and going for  itâ€”winning by learning, growing, and stretchingâ€”and helping others do the same  through skill development and sales coaching. </p>\r\n', '', '//c9890511.ssl.cf2.rackcdn.com/71333335741.jpg', 'Roula Crews', 5, 1, 0, '', '', '', '', '2012-03-15 20:35:01', '2012-06-04 12:30:35'),
(16, 'Managing Cash Flow with Lee Werner', '', '2012-05-17 11:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'CST', 1, '<p>Do you have a firm grip on your companyâ€™s lifebloodâ€”cash flow? If youâ€™re  closing sales, but still having a hard time meeting your financial commitments,  chances are you have a cash flow problem.</p>\r\n<p>Bring your questions on how to get your cash flow into  tip-top shape to this Finance Coach Chat with Lee Werner, an accomplished  coach, trainer and professional in the Finance arena. If youâ€™re having trouble  with your receivables or any other that impacts your cash flow, this is the  opportunity to ask for some help on Managing Your Cash Flow.</p>\r\n<p>As a thirty-year accounting professional, Lee Werner has a  passion to help business owners take their businesses to a higher level of  profitability by finding ways to increase revenues, reducing operational costs  and increasing effectiveness. Lee has accomplished this through coaching,  training, and supervising both entry-level accounting and bookkeeping staff as  well as corporate and C-Suite Executive level staff and board members.  Currently Lee is the Chief Finance Officer for a nationally known private  school. Lee is also an entrepreneur and consultant with experience in a variety  of accounting systems software, including being a Quickbooks Pro Advisor  whereby he trains clients in the use of QuickBooks accounting software.  </p>\r\n', '', '//c9890511.ssl.cf2.rackcdn.com/71333335810.jpg', 'Lee Werner', 5, 1, 0, '', '', '', '', '2012-03-15 20:36:08', '2012-06-04 12:30:35'),
(17, 'SEO, SEM, and Social Networks', '', '2012-05-31 11:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'CST', 1, '<p>You&rsquo;ve heard how important it is to search engine optimize  your website. You understand that to reach potential customers, you need to  engage on social networks. But maybe you can&rsquo;t figure out that first step to  take. Or, perhaps you&rsquo;ve tried and either didn&rsquo;t get the results you hoped for  or you need to understand what your next step should be.</p>\r\n<p>This Marketing Coach Chat with social media guru Dean  DeLisle is the perfect opportunity to get the answers you need to get started  or keep moving. Come prepared to tell Dean what you&rsquo;ve done and what results  you&rsquo;ve had and see where he thinks you need to head next. Tell him a bit about  your company and find out where he thinks is the best place to start in your  efforts on SEO, SEM and Social Networks.</p>\r\n<p>As CEO of Forward  Progress, Dean leads his core team to provide integrated marketing solutions  using a proven coaching and consulting methodology in driving business  growth.  Committed to delivering both  &ldquo;Lowest Cost per Lead&rdquo; and &ldquo;Converting Leads to Sales,&rdquo; Forward Progress has  helped over 2,000 corporate clients assess and improve their online marketing  and social networking results and has trained over 25,000 people in over 20  countries with their online programs.  As  an experienced CEO and business owner, Dean also coaches senior executives in  publicly and privately held companies, using his proprietary Power Plan System  to identify the appropriate strategy, map out a clear direction, structure the  team and execute the plan within an aggressive timeframe.</p>\r\n', '', '//c9890511.ssl.cf2.rackcdn.com/71333335860.jpg', 'Dean DeLisle ', 5, 1, 0, '', '', '', '', '2012-03-15 20:37:04', '2012-06-04 12:30:35'),
(18, 'Making an Introduction with Impact with Barbara Lopez', '', '2012-06-14 11:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'CST', 1, '<p>You only have 30 seconds to gain someoneâ€™s interest in what  you do.  Have you mastered your elevator  pitchâ€”or do you think it could use a little work?</p>\r\n<p>Either way, join us for this Marketing Coach Chat with  Barbara Lopez, The Elevator Pitch Coach. Bring your elevator pitch to this Chat  and see what Barbara thinks of it and what advice she might have to make it  even better. Maybe youâ€™ll even be the one that she says has exactly whatâ€™s  needed for Making an Introduction with Impact. </p>\r\n<p>Barbara Lopez believes that everything in business STARTS  with a BRIGHT introduction.  Barbara has  been a professional commercial writer since 2003 through her business,  Brightfarm Introductions.  She has  written commercials for corporate businesses, entrepreneurs, solo-preneurs,  nonprofit organizations, direct sales professionals, and countless small  businesses across the country.  Barbara  has turned the process she uses for creating award winning <em>visual</em> commercials into an easy to 4-step process for professionals  to use to create their <em>verbal</em> commercial, their elevator pitch. As The Elevator Pitch Coach, Barbara now  writes professional elevator pitches for business professionals, as well as  offers private coaching, workshops and teleclasses.</p>\r\n', '', '//c9890511.ssl.cf2.rackcdn.com/71333376521.jpg', 'Barbara Lopez', 5, 1, 0, '', '', '', '', '2012-03-15 20:38:03', '2012-06-04 12:30:35'),
(19, 'Creating a Sales Environment with Kirsten Zoub', '', '2012-06-28 11:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'CST', 1, '<p>As a small business owner, you know you and your sales team  have responsibility when it comes to your companyâ€™s sales. But did you know  that everyone else in the company also has a sales role to play? Thatâ€™s right, to  achieve your business goals, you need to have every person in your firm engaged  in some selling activity.</p>\r\n<p>If you have questions about just how to do this, then join  this Sales Coach Chat with Kirsten Zoub, a professional growth coach. Sheâ€™ll  answer your questions about how to make sure youâ€™re Creating a Sales  Environment for your company.</p>\r\n<p>Kirsten Zoub is a Serial Entrepreneur, Director of Sales, Speaker,  Coach and Group Facilitator at Wright Leadership Institute.  For the last 25 years, Kirsten has  successfully started and run businesses in a variety of fields such as freight  brokering, art publishing, real estate, and health and wellness.  She now uses her wealth of experience to  empower and serve a diverse population of business owners and sales executives  including top level CEOs. In the past year, she has helped her clients achieve  and surpass their personal and professional goals, supporting some to as much  as double their annual income. </p>\r\n', '', '//c9890511.ssl.cf2.rackcdn.com/71333375858.jpg', 'Kirsten Zoub', 5, 1, 0, '', '', '', '', '2012-03-15 20:38:54', '2012-06-04 12:30:35'),
(20, 'Managing Employees, Contractors and More with Michelle Binks', '', '2012-07-26 11:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'CST', 1, '<p>As a small business owner, you may have several employees  or work with contractors, but chances are you donâ€™t have a Human Resources  Manager. And the chances are also good that you have lots of HR questions.<br />\r\n  <br />\r\n  Bring those questions to the HR Coach Chat with Michelle  Binks, a seasoned HR professional. Ask her those nagging questions you have  regarding annual reviews, hiring and firing, or benefits. Ask her everything  you need to know about Managing Employees, Contractors and More.</p>\r\n<p>Michelle Binks is a human resource professional with 20  years of diversified human resource experience.   She spent a large portion of her career providing and overseeing human  resources, safety, labor relations and the hiring function for small to mid-sized  manufacturing companies, ranging from stand alone facilities employing 150  employees to those having over 26 facilities worldwide.  </p>\r\n<p>Since leaving the corporate world, she has opened her own  firm, HR Consulting Solutions, and has consulted in a host of industries  including: manufacturing, construction, financial institutions, information  technology, distribution, medical, restaurant and the not for profit. </p>\r\n', '', '//c9890511.ssl.cf2.rackcdn.com/71333375927.jpg', 'Michelle Binks', 3, 1, 0, '', '', '', '', '2012-03-15 20:41:58', '2012-06-04 12:30:35'),
(21, 'Planning for Your Business with Jackie B. Peterson', '', '2012-08-23 11:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'CST', 1, '<p>Growing your business takes a lot more than just luckâ€”it  takes planning. A business plan is more  than a list of marketing tactics that you hope will result in sales; itâ€™s about  setting goals for your business and then strategically planning for it.</p>\r\n<p>So, how is your business plan coming? If you need help  making sure youâ€™ve defined all the elements of the plan, then youâ€™ll want to  participate in this Business Growth Coach Chat with Jackie B. Peterson, a  business and strategic advisor.  She can  answer your questions on how to create a plan and how to use it both internally  and externally--and any other questions you have regarding Planning for Your  Business.</p>\r\n<p> Jackie B. Peterson, author of <em>Better, Smarter, Richer: Seven Business  Principles for Creative Entrepreneurs and Solopreneurs</em>, has worked with  small businesses, solopreneurs and freelance entrepreneurs for over 30 years.  Jackie herself is an entrepreneur, business adviser and CPA. Jackie currently  works as a strategic adviser/instructor for the Small Business Development  Center of Portland Community College and maintains an independent consulting  practice.</p>\r\n', '', '//c9890511.ssl.cf2.rackcdn.com/71333375987.jpg', 'Jackie B. Peterson', 5, 1, 0, '', '', '', '', '2012-03-15 20:42:53', '2012-06-04 12:30:35'),
(22, 'Charging What Youâ€™re Worth with <!-- mp_trans_disable_start -->Jackie B. Peterson<!-- mp_trans_disable_end  -->', '', '2012-09-06 11:00:00', '2032-01-01 00:00:00', 'CST', 1, '&lt;p&gt;Businesses frequently charge for their services using a &amp;ldquo;cost plus&amp;rdquo; model&amp;mdash;they cover their costs and then add something to the top. Do you know how much to add to the top? Have you considered a different approach that might relate more to the &lt;em&gt;value&lt;/em&gt; of your service rather than the cost of it?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;If you struggle with trying to define what your pricing structure should look like, then join us for this Marketing Chat with strategic and business advisor Jackie B. Peterson. Tell her what you do and ask for her suggestions on how to determine what your pricing model should be. Ask her specifics on how to understand the value of your products or services. In short, ask her questions so that you know you are Charging What You&amp;rsquo;re Worth.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Jackie B. Peterson, author of &lt;em&gt;Better, Smarter, Richer: Seven Business Principles for Creative Entrepreneurs and Solopreneurs&lt;/em&gt;, has worked with small businesses, solopreneurs and freelance entrepreneurs for over 30 years. Jackie herself is an entrepreneur, business adviser and CPA. Jackie currently works as a strategic adviser/instructor for the Small Business Development Center of Portland Community College and maintains an independent consulting practice.&lt;/p&gt;', '', '//c9890511.ssl.cf2.rackcdn.com/71333376037.jpg', 'Jackie B. Peterson', 5, 1, 0, '', '', '', '', '2012-03-15 20:43:57', '2012-06-04 12:30:35'),
(24, 'P&Ls, Income Statements and More with Lee Werner', '', '2012-10-18 11:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'CST', 1, '<p>The thought of working on your P&amp;L and your companyâ€™s income  statement sends shudders up your spine, but you know that doing so is essential  to understanding the financial health of your business. Are you doing them  correctly? Are you getting the true picture of where your company stands?</p>\r\n<p>If these are the kinds of questions that pop into your mind  when it comes to these topics, this Finance Coach Chat with Lee Werner, an  accomplished coach, trainer and professional in the Finance arena, is exactly  what you need. Lee can answer the questions you have about how to put together  and utilize these financial reports. Nowâ€™s the time to make sure you understand  how to work with P&amp;Ls, Income Statements and More.</p>\r\n<p>As a thirty-year accounting professional, Lee  Werner has a passion to help business owners take their businesses to a higher  level of profitability by finding ways to increase revenues, reducing  operational costs and increasing effectiveness. Lee has accomplished this  through coaching, training, and supervising both entry-level accounting and  bookkeeping staff as well as corporate and C-Suite Executive level staff and  board members. Currently Lee is the Chief Finance Officer for a nationally  known private school. Lee is also an entrepreneur and consultant with  experience in a variety of accounting systems software, including being a  Quickbooks Pro Advisor whereby he trains clients in the use of QuickBooks  accounting software. </p>\r\n', '', '//c9890511.ssl.cf2.rackcdn.com/71333376155.jpg', 'Lee Werner', 5, 1, 0, '', '', '', '', '2012-03-15 20:45:34', '2012-06-04 12:30:35'),
(25, 'Which Marketing Tactics Are Best for Me? with Michelle Lanter Smith', '', '2012-10-25 11:00:00', '2032-01-01 00:00:00', 'CST', 1, '&lt;p&gt;There are a plethora of marketing tactics that you, as a small business owner, can use to grow your business&amp;mdash;some you might know about and some you haven&amp;rsquo;t heard of yet. Do you know if you&amp;rsquo;re using the right tactics to achieve the objectives and goals you&amp;rsquo;ve set? How can you tell?&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Marketing strategist and coach Michelle Lanter Smith can answer these and other questions for you in this Marketing Coach Chat. Let her know what you&amp;rsquo;re trying to accomplish and she can suggest tactics that will bring results. You don&amp;rsquo;t have to&amp;nbsp; try to figure it out on your own; let Michelle help you find the answer to that question, &amp;ldquo;Which Marketing Tactics Are Best for Me?&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;Michelle Lanter Smith is a nationally recognized marketing strategist, speaker, and coach.&amp;nbsp; She has coached more than 2,000 firms in finding their sweet spot&amp;mdash;helping them determine their unique business identity&amp;mdash;and pumping their sales volumes to new heights.&amp;nbsp; She is a pioneer in building and implementing experiential, integrated marketing campaigns for companies such as IBM, American Family Insurance, McDonald&amp;rsquo;s, Coca-Cola, Walgreens and mid-sized industrial companies.&amp;nbsp; Not only have her campaigns resulted in awards in Hispanic and Business to Business marketing segments, but they&amp;rsquo;ve also increased her clients&amp;rsquo; market share and generated millions in new revenue. &amp;nbsp;Committed to educating entrepreneurs on using marketing to grow their business, Michelle frequently blogs and speaks on &lt;em&gt;Finding Your Sweet Spot.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;', '', '//c9890511.ssl.cf2.rackcdn.com/71333376270.jpg', 'Michelle Lanter Smith', 5, 1, 0, '', '', '', 'Congratulations You are registered for the Business Accelerator Entrepreneurial Hub on May 31, 2012. The topic is How to Focus Your Marketing and Develop Your Unique Value Proposition.The program begins at 500 pm, with checkin and networking beginning at 430 pm. Coffee and light refreshments will be served. The program ends at 630 pm. The Entrepreneurial Hub will be held at the Oregon Medical Association, located at 11740 SW 68th Parkway, Ste 100, Portland, OR 97223.We look forward to having you join us. Because seating is limited, should you need to cancel, please send an email to Teri Latter attlatter@brillantemcm.com', '2012-03-15 20:46:20', '2012-04-03 12:18:51'),
(26, 'Driving Your Business to the Next Level with Kirsten Zoub', '', '2012-11-15 11:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'CST', 1, '<p>Your business is moving along at a steady rate, but you  know it could do better. What will it take to move it up to that next level?  Time, money, resources?</p>\r\n<p>Let professional growth coach Kirsten Zoub help you sort  out what it takes in this Business Growth Coach Chat. Get her help with  roadblocks you might be facing to move forward. Ask her for ideas on how to get  started with Driving Your Business to the Next Level.</p>\r\n<p>Kirsten Zoub is a Serial Entrepreneur, Director of Sales, Speaker,  Coach and Group Facilitator at Wright Leadership Institute.  For the last 25 years, Kirsten has  successfully started and run businesses in a variety of fields such as freight  brokering, art publishing, real estate, and health and wellness.  She now uses her wealth of experience to  empower and serve a diverse population of business owners and sales executives  including top level CEOs. In the past year, she has helped her clients achieve  and surpass their personal and professional goals, supporting some to as much  as double their annual income. </p>\r\n', '', '//c9890511.ssl.cf2.rackcdn.com/71333376353.jpg', 'Kirsten Zoub', 5, 1, 0, '', '', '', '', '2012-03-15 20:47:09', '2012-06-04 12:30:35'),
(27, 'Breaking Through, Getting the Appointment with Roula Crews', '', '2012-12-13 11:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'CST', 1, '<p>Are you satisfied with your call-to-appointment ratio?  Whatâ€™s getting in the way? Maybe itâ€™s the gatekeepers or maybe your opening  intro isnâ€™t strong enough.</p>\r\n<p>Whateverâ€™s stopping you from getting more appointments,  professional sales coach Roula Crews can help you during this Sales Coach Chat.  If you consistently run into the same problem, get her advice on how to change  your approach.  Maybe youâ€™re not sure  what the issue isâ€”bring it to her and sheâ€™ll help you figure out what it takes  to start Breaking Through and Getting the Appointment.</p>\r\n<p>Roula Crews is a founding partner  of Hi-Impact Marketing &amp; Sales Solutions, Inc. and has played a key role in  the growth of the Business Accelerator Program through her of her ability to connect and partner with  local and national multicultural chambers. Through her  one-on-one sales training and coaching, sheâ€™s helped clients increase their  sales by as much as 20%.  With over  twenty years of sales experience, Roula loves aiming high and going for  itâ€”winning by learning, growing, and stretchingâ€”and helping others do the same  through skill development and sales coaching. </p>\r\n', '', '//c9890511.ssl.cf2.rackcdn.com/71333376424.jpg', 'Roula Crews', 5, 1, 0, '', '', '', '', '2012-03-15 20:47:52', '2012-06-04 12:30:35'),
(32, 'Social Media with Dean DeLisle', '', '2012-09-27 11:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'CST', 1, '<p>With the constant changes and innovations in the world of social media, itâ€™s hard to keep up with everything and to determine which social media vehicles will serve your company best. And if you do figure that out, a new social media site is introduced and you wonder if thatâ€™s where should be!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Join our social media expert, Dean DeLisle for this Marketing Coach Chat to find out what you should be doing and how to do it. Hereâ€™s your chance to bring all your questions regarding the ins and outs of social media to the person who can help you understand how to drive business growth through Social Media.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As CEO of Forward Progress, Dean leads his core team to provide integrated marketing solutions using a proven coaching and consulting methodology in driving business growth.  Committed to delivering both â€œLowest Cost per Leadâ€ and â€œConverting Leads to Sales,â€ Forward Progress has helped over 2,000 corporate clients assess and improve their online marketing and social networking results and has trained over 25,000 people in over 20 countries with their online programs.  As an experienced CEO and business owner, Dean also coaches senior executives in publicly and privately held companies, using his proprietary Power Plan System to identify the appropriate strategy, map out a clear direction, structure the team and execute the plan within an aggressive timeframe.</p>', '', '//c9890511.ssl.cf2.rackcdn.com/71333376583.jpg', 'Dean DeLisle', 5, 1, 0, '', '', '', '', '2012-03-20 21:52:16', '2012-04-03 12:19:13'),
